{"id":"https://genegraph.clinicalgenome.org/r/47cec004-d3c0-4306-a0f6-954fc911085dv2.0","type":"EvidenceStrengthAssertion","dc:description":"HOMER2 was described in association with autosomal dominant nonsyndromic hearing loss in 2015 by Azaiez et al. (25816005). At least 1 missense variant and 1 frameshift variant have been reported in humans (25816005, 30047143). Variants in this gene segregated with disease in 17 additional family members. Evidence supporting this gene-disease association includes case-level, segregation and experimental evidence. In summary, there is moderate evidence to support this gene-disease association. While more evidence is needed to establish this association definitively, no convincing contradictory evidence has emerged. This classification was approved by the ClinGen Hearing Loss Working Group on 8/31/2020.","dc:isVersionOf":"https://genegraph.clinicalgenome.org/r/47cec004-d3c0-4306-a0f6-954fc911085d","GCISnapshot":"https://genegraph.clinicalgenome.org/r/9158c2a6-f11b-47b4-ac7d-45471f7255a1","calculatedEvidenceStrength":"Moderate","changes":[{"id":"cg:summaryChange"},{"id":"cg:sopChange"}],"contributions":[{"id":"https://genegraph.clinicalgenome.org/r/9158c2a6-f11b-47b4-ac7d-45471f7255a1_contrib","agent":"https://genegraph.clinicalgenome.org/agent/10007","date":"2020-08-31T17:00:00.000Z","role":"Approver"},{"id":"https://genegraph.clinicalgenome.org/r/9158c2a6-f11b-47b4-ac7d-45471f7255a1_publish_contrib","agent":"https://genegraph.clinicalgenome.org/agent/10007","date":"2020-09-16T19:23:38.512Z","role":"Publisher"}],"curationReasonDescription":"","evidence":[{"id":"https://genegraph.clinicalgenome.org/r/9158c2a6-f11b-47b4-ac7d-45471f7255a1_overall_genetic_evidence_line","type":"EvidenceLine","evidence":[{"id":"https://genegraph.clinicalgenome.org/r/9158c2a6-f11b-47b4-ac7d-45471f7255a1_seg_el","type":"EvidenceLine","evidence":[{"id":"https://genegraph.clinicalgenome.org/r/74496ea8-e876-4fe9-bee1-bde1392030f4_proband_segregation","type"